	<item>
		<title>By: crimfan</title>
		<link>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-lines-grooves/exporing-bossa-nova.html#comment-16276</link>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[crimfan]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 22 Jul 2015 13:13:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/?p=5712#comment-16276</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[I seem to get bossa nova pretty well, though if the drummer doesn&#039;t, you&#039;re kind of screwed. 

A tune like Blue Bossa is great because you end up learning how little you can play to keep the bossa groove going. I remember one point when the whole thing really &quot;clicked&quot; which was a cool feeling! 

Cm7 Cm7 Fm7 Bb7
Dm7b5 G7b9 Cm7 Cm7
Ebm7 Ab7 DbM7 DbM7        (key change!)
Dm7b5 G7b9 Cm7 Cm7

For instance, there are several ii-Vs in the standard chart for it but you can frequently blow right past the ii, or create instant variations by leaving it out sometimes and putting it in other times. Either way it fits and it creates variation while leaving plenty of space. 


Kenny Dorham deserves to be remembered a lot more than he is, truly one of the greats. I want to work on La Mesha next.]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I seem to get bossa nova pretty well, though if the drummer doesn&#8217;t, you&#8217;re kind of screwed. </p>
<p>A tune like Blue Bossa is great because you end up learning how little you can play to keep the bossa groove going. I remember one point when the whole thing really &#8220;clicked&#8221; which was a cool feeling! </p>
<p>Cm7 Cm7 Fm7 Bb7<br />
Dm7b5 G7b9 Cm7 Cm7<br />
Ebm7 Ab7 DbM7 DbM7        (key change!)<br />
Dm7b5 G7b9 Cm7 Cm7</p>
<p>For instance, there are several ii-Vs in the standard chart for it but you can frequently blow right past the ii, or create instant variations by leaving it out sometimes and putting it in other times. Either way it fits and it creates variation while leaving plenty of space. </p>
<p>Kenny Dorham deserves to be remembered a lot more than he is, truly one of the greats. I want to work on La Mesha next.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
